# Cursor Rules for Sports Engine (Next.js App Router + Supabase + Tailwind)

## Project Context

- This is a Next.js 13+ App Router project.
- API endpoints live under `app/api/**/route.ts`.
- Supabase is used for auth and data (Postgres backend).
- Tailwind CSS is available and should be used for styling.

## Sports Engine Subsystem

- All sports analytics logic should be encapsulated under:
  - `lib/sports-engine/**` for core logic (ingestion, prediction, decision, db helpers)
  - `app/api/sports/**` for API route handlers
  - `app/sports/**` for UI pages
- The system is for analytics and predictions only.
- It must NOT provide betting instructions, tips, or recommendations.
- It may provide:
  - probabilities
  - confidence levels
  - decision categories (e.g. HIGH_CONFIDENCE, MEDIUM_CONFIDENCE, LOW_CONFIDENCE, NO_ACTION)

## Tech & Style Rules

- Use TypeScript for all new files.
- Use Next.js App Router conventions (`route.ts`, server components by default).
- Use Supabase JS client for database operations.
- Use Tailwind CSS for layout and styling.
- Prefer small, composable modules over monolithic files.

## Safety & Scope

- Do NOT implement any betting, staking, or gambling logic.
- Do NOT output or encode any logic that tells the user what to bet on.
- The system is strictly for analytics, probabilities, and decision categories.

## Future-Proofing

- Design the sports-engine so it can be extracted into a separate service later.
- Keep API contracts clean and versionable.
- Keep UI components reusable and easy to restyle into a more premium design.
